85.6	Combustion	Combustion	Combustion ( ) or burning is the sequence of exothermic chemical reactions between a fuel and an oxidant accompanied by the production of heat and conversion of chemical species. The release of heat can result in the production of light in the form of either glowing or a flame. Fuels of interest often include organic compounds (especially hydrocarbons) in the gas, liquid or solid phase.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3c/Et_baal.jpg/200px-Et_baal.jpg
